\import{base-macros}

\taxon{Definition}

\title{Universal closure w.r.t variables}

\p{
  If a formula #{C} has a set of free variables:
}
##{
  \cf{FV}(C) = \{x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_n\}
}
\p{
  Then we can denote the universal closure #{\forall^*} as representing the universal quantification over all those free variables, i.e. [(1)](hetzlkloibhofer2025):
}
##{
  \forall^* C \equiv \forall x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_n.\ C
}
